    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Selliguea soridens are attributed to its antimicrobial activity, which is primarily due to the presence of flavonoids and saponins, displaying potent antibacterial and antifungal effects. Additionally, this plant exhibits antioxidant properties, mediated by volatile oils and phenolic compounds, which help to neutralize free radicals and protect against oxidative stress. Its anti-inflammatory activity is attributed to the presence of sesquiterpenes and saponins, which inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes and cytokines, leading to reduced inflammation and swelling. Furthermore, Selliguea soridens has been found to possess analgesic and hepatoprotective properties, with the bioactive compounds, including flavonoids and terpenoids, exerting analgesic effects by inhibiting pain mediators and protecting the liver against damage by scavenging free radicals and modulating inflammatory responses. The hepatoprotective effects of this plant are also attributed to the presence of saponins and sesquiterpenes, which help to regenerate liver cells and maintain liver function.",
